<dl class="row">
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Angel') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('The angel stage is aimed at getting a new company started.  Typically, it is a relatively small amount sourced from family, friends, individual angel investors or angel investor groups.') }}</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Seed') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('This is the first official funding round for a company, it can also involve angel investors or venture capital (VC) companies.  This round helps a company through its first steps like marketing, product development etc. and usually ranges from around $10 000 up to $1/$2 million.') }}</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Series A') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('This series of funding is used to optimise your product or service.  You are already established with a clear revenue stream or user base but need to optimize your business model in order to create a sustainable business. Series A funding is generally between $2 million and $15 million.') }}</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Series B') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('This stage of funding is used to consolidate your business. You already have a successful revenue generating business model but want to grow your company by hiring new talent, investing in advertising, sales and making sure your company has a solid base for future expansion.  Series B typically involves amounts of $7 million to $10 million.') }}</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Series C') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('Your company is relatively well established and successful but you need to achieve scale.  This is where Series C funding comes into play. You want to create new products, enter new markets, or even acquire a competitor. At this stage more risk averse investors like banks, private equity, or hedge funds may start investing in your company.') }}</dd>
    <dt class="col-sm-3 col-lg-2">{{ __('Series D/E') }}</dt>
    <dd class="col-sm-9 col-lg-10 mb-3">{{ __('It is unusual for companies to continue on to Series D or E funding.  At this stage your company is large and well-established with a valuation over $50 million or even $100 million.  This stage can be considered a final push at expansion and consolidation before an IPO.') }}</dd>
</dl>
